subject: Re: [Read_Alphabet] dictionary, script not working
msgSnippet: Hi Paul, I don t use Windows either, but if you unzip the file QsConverter_1_2_1.zip and look in the resulting directory you ll find the dictionary file
messageBody:
Hi Paul,

I don't use Windows either, but if you unzip the file QsConverter_1_2_1.zip and look in the resulting directory you'll find the dictionary file QS_Dict_TextOnly.txt. I converted this into a file in Rich Text Format, available here:

http://staff.washington.edu/freeman/qs/qs_dict.rtf

It's a big file, but I still find it usable as a reference by simply searching for words that I'm having difficulty transcribing. When I tried converting it to PDF format it was too large to be useful. I'd be happy to upload this file to the group website if others would like it to be there.

Note that this file does not contain a single instance of QS letter #34 ("On" in Jon Zuck's nomenclature).

Ted


On 10/9/07, Paul Tremblay <phthenry@...> wrote:

I can't access two resources from the files. The first is the
QS_Converter, written for Windows. Is there any source for this script
so that it would work with other platforms? What would be especially
helpful is to simply have the convertor dictionary that it uses.

Second, I can't unzip the PDF dictionaries. I have downloaded both zip
files, but when I try to unzip the second, I get an error.

Paul
